<div id="review_2577236807" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2577236807" />
    <a title="Shweta Kumar" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7037199-shweta-kumar"><img alt="Shweta Kumar" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1322115558p2/7037199.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2577236807?book_show_action=true">Oct 30, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shweta Kumar" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shweta Kumar" href="/user/show/7037199-shweta-kumar">Shweta Kumar</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2577236807" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1837463303945019547">This novel is a well-written train wreck. While the modern part of the novel is relatable, the British Raj part is barely researched in terms of societal set-up and even amenities available at the time. <br/>The basic writing is good, but the utter lack of research, even the basic kind, was a complete let down. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


