  <span id="freeText3063835048406744800" style="display:none">One of the reasons I read is to visit places in time that I will never see, meeting people I will never know. If the people and the story are interesting, I savor an in-depth experience.<br /><br />The Storytellers Secret is a long, moving tale about a woman who, after experiencing several miscarriages, goes on a quest of discovery about her family roots in India and discovers truths about herself and her marriage in the process. I enjoyed learning about the culture of her grandmother's village and time during the Raj. </span>
